Document: Default editor shortcuts
Path: godot/tutorials/editor/default_key_mapping.rst
Summary: This section explains how to customize Godot editor shortcuts and notes context-specific key mappings and macOS differences.

Many Godot editor functions can be executed with keyboard shortcuts. This page lists functions which have associated shortcuts by default, but many others are available for customization in editor settings as well. To change keys associated with these and other actions navigate to Editor > Editor Settings > Shortcuts.

While some actions are universal, a lot of shortcuts are specific to individual tools. For this reason it is possible for some key combinations to be assigned to more than one function. The correct action will be performed depending on the context.

Note: While Windows and Linux builds of the editor share most of the default settings, some shortcuts may differ for macOS version. This is done for better integration of the editor into macOS ecosystem. Users fluent with standard shortcuts on that OS should find Godot Editor's default key mapping intuitive.
---CHUNK---
Document: default_key_mapping
Path: godot/tutorials/editor/default_key_mapping.rst
Summary: This section lists default key mappings for general editor actions in Godot, including shortcuts for Windows, Linux, and macOS, and their corresponding editor settings.

- Open 2D Workspace: Ctrl + F1 (Windows, Linux); Cmd + Ctrl + 1 (macOS); editor/editor_2d.
- Open 3D Workspace: Ctrl + F2 (Windows, Linux); Cmd + Ctrl + 2 (macOS); editor/editor_3d.
- Open Script Editor: Ctrl + F3 (Windows, Linux); Cmd + Ctrl + 3 (macOS); editor/editor_script.
- Search Help: F1 (Windows, Linux); Opt + Space (macOS); editor/editor_help.
- Distraction Free Mode: Ctrl + Shift + F11 (Windows, Linux); Cmd + Shift + D (macOS); editor/distraction_free_mode.
- Next Scene Tab: Ctrl + Tab (Windows, Linux); Ctrl + Tab (macOS); editor/next_tab.
- Previous Scene Tab: Ctrl + Shift + Tab (Windows, Linux); Ctrl + Shift + Tab (macOS); editor/prev_tab.
- Filter Files: Ctrl + Alt + P (Windows, Linux); Opt + Cmd + P (macOS); editor/filter_files.
- Open Scene: Ctrl + O (Windows, Linux); Cmd + O (macOS); editor/open_scene.
- Close Scene: Ctrl + Shift + W (Windows, Linux); Cmd + W (macOS); editor/close_scene.
- Reopen Closed Scene: Ctrl + Shift + T (Windows, Linux); Cmd + Shift + T (macOS); editor/reopen_closed_scene.
- Save Scene: Ctrl + S (Windows, Linux); Cmd + S (macOS); editor/save_scene.
- Save Scene As: Ctrl + Shift + S (Windows, Linux); Cmd + Shift + S (macOS); editor/save_scene_as.
- Save All Scenes: Ctrl + Shift + Alt + S (Windows, Linux); Cmd + Shift + Opt + S (macOS); editor/save_all_scenes.
- Quick Open: Shift + Alt + O (Windows, Linux); Cmd + Ctrl + O (macOS); editor/quick_open.
- Quick Open Scene: Ctrl + Shift + O (Windows, Linux); Cmd + Shift + O (macOS); editor/quick_open_scene.
- Quick Open Script: Ctrl + Alt + O (Windows, Linux); Opt + Cmd + O (macOS); editor/quick_open_script.
- Undo: Ctrl + Z (Windows, Linux); Cmd + Z (macOS); editor/undo.
- Redo: Ctrl + Shift + Z (Windows, Linux); Cmd + Shift + Z (macOS); editor/redo.
- Quit: Ctrl + Q (Windows, Linux); Cmd + Q (macOS); editor/file_quit.
- Quit to Project List: Ctrl + Shift + Q (Windows, Linux); Shift + Opt + Q (macOS); editor/quit_to_project_list.
- Take Screenshot: Ctrl + F12 (Windows, Linux); Cmd + F12 (macOS); editor/take_screenshot.
- Toggle Fullscreen: Shift + F11 (Windows, Linux); Cmd + Ctrl + F (macOS); editor/fullscreen_mode.
- Play: F5 (Windows, Linux); Cmd + B (macOS); editor/play.
- Pause Scene: F7 (Windows, Linux); Cmd + Ctrl + Y (macOS); editor/pause_scene.
- Stop: F8 (Windows, Linux); Cmd + . (macOS); editor/stop.
- Play Scene: F6 (Windows, Linux); Cmd + R (macOS); editor/play_scene.
- Play Custom Scene: Ctrl + Shift + F5 (Windows, Linux); Cmd + Shift + R (macOS); editor/play_custom_scene.
- Expand Bottom Panel: Shift + F12 (Windows, Linux); Shift + F12 (macOS); editor/bottom_panel_expand.
- Command Palette: Ctrl + Shift + P (Windows, Linux); Cmd + Shift + P (macOS); editor/command_palette.
---CHUNK---
Document: Default Key Mapping
Path: godot/tutorials/editor/default_key_mapping.rst
Summary: This section lists default key mappings for Godot editor bottom panels.

Only bottom panels that are always available have a default shortcut assigned. Others must be manually bound in the Editor Settings if desired.

*   Toggle Last Opened Panel: Ctrl + J (Windows, Linux / macOS). Editor setting: editor/toggle_last_opened_bottom_panel.
*   Toggle Animation Bottom Panel: Alt + N (Windows, Linux / macOS). Editor setting: bottom_panels/toggle_animation_bottom_panel.
*   Toggle Audio Bottom Panel: Alt + A (Windows, Linux / macOS). Editor setting: bottom_panels/toggle_audio_bottom_panel.
*   Toggle Debugger Bottom Panel: Alt + D (Windows, Linux / macOS). Editor setting: bottom_panels/toggle_debugger_bottom_panel.
*   Toggle FileSystem Bottom Panel: Alt + F (Windows, Linux / macOS). Editor setting: bottom_panels/toggle_filesystem_bottom_panel.
*   Toggle Output Bottom Panel: Alt + O (Windows, Linux / macOS). Editor setting: bottom_panels/toggle_output_bottom_panel.
*   Toggle Shader Editor Bottom Panel: Alt + S (Windows, Linux / macOS). Editor setting: bottom_panels/toggle_shader_editor_bottom_panel.
---CHUNK---
