Document: TileSet Editor
Path: godot/tutorials/editor/default_key_mapping.rst
Summary: This section lists the default key mappings for various actions within the Godot TileSet Editor.

TileSet Editor
*   Next Coordinate (Windows, Linux: PgDown, macOS: PgDown): Editor setting tileset_editor/next_shape
*   Previous Coordinate (Windows, Linux: PgUp, macOS: PgUp): Editor setting tileset_editor/previous_shape
*   Region Mode (Windows, Linux: 1, macOS: 1): Editor setting tileset_editor/editmode_region
*   Collision Mode (Windows, Linux: 2, macOS: 2): Editor setting tileset_editor/editmode_collision
*   Occlusion Mode (Windows, Linux: 3, macOS: 3): Editor setting tileset_editor/editmode_occlusion
*   Navigation Mode (Windows, Linux: 4, macOS: 4): Editor setting tileset_editor/editmode_navigation
*   Bitmask Mode (Windows, Linux: 5, macOS: 5): Editor setting tileset_editor/editmode_bitmask
*   Priority Mode (Windows, Linux: 6, macOS: 6): Editor setting tileset_editor/editmode_priority
*   Icon Mode (Windows, Linux: 7, macOS: 7): Editor setting tileset_editor/editmode_icon
*   Z Index Mode (Windows, Linux: 8, macOS: 8): Editor setting tileset_editor/editmode_z_index
---CHUNK---
Document: GridMap Editor
Path: godot/tutorials/editor/default_key_mapping.rst
Summary: This section lists the default key mappings for actions within the Godot GridMap editor.

GridMap Editor
*   Previous Floor: 1 (Windows, Linux), 1 (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/previous_floor
*   Next Floor: 3 (Windows, Linux), 3 (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/next_floor
*   Edit X Axis: Shift + Z (Windows, Linux), Shift + Z (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/edit_x_axis
*   Edit Y Axis: Shift + X (Windows, Linux), Shift + X (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/edit_y_axis
*   Edit Z Axis: Shift + C (Windows, Linux), Shift + C (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/edit_z_axis
*   Transform: T (Windows, Linux), T (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/transform_tool
*   Selection: Q (Windows, Linux), Q (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/selection_tool
*   Erase: W (Windows, Linux), W (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/erase_tool
*   Paint: E (Windows, Linux), E (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/paint_tool
*   Pick: R (Windows, Linux), R (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/pick_tool
*   Fill: Z (Windows, Linux), Z (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/fill_tool
*   Move: X (Windows, Linux), X (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/move_tool
*   Duplicate: C (Windows, Linux), C (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/duplicate_tool
*   Delete: V (Windows, Linux), V (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/delete_tool
*   Cursor Rotate X: A (Windows, Linux), A (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/cursor_rotate_x
*   Cursor Rotate Y: S (Windows, Linux), S (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/cursor_rotate_y
*   Cursor Rotate Z: D (Windows, Linux), D (macOS). Editor setting: grid_map/cursor_rotate_z
